<dl id="un1013t"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="un1" href="#un1013">UN1: </a>  <a href="../../ff/unbs/un1all.htm#un1013t"> (NLI.3) 13(t)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> It&apos;s the Logos who suffers at every moment: <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">A Study in Christian Gnosticism&rdquo; 327: The general Christian could not understand that <mark>it is the Logos who suffers at every moment</mark> of time in every human soul, who dies in every human body, who rises in every human spirit. And yet He suffers none of those separate things; His is an Eternal Passion that is Pain and Pleasure perpetually united. <small> <a name="THRdec1908" href="/udra/udex.htm#thrdec1908"><cite title="source">The Theosophical Review</cite></a> (December 1908), G. R. S. Mead, &ldquo;The Secret of Jesus</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Copied to <a name="un4011cf" href="un4all.htm#un4011cf">UN4 (NLI.5A):011(cf)</a> for <cite>UG</cite> 9.62. </mm> </dd></dl>
